Trajectory of anterior medial temporal lobe involvement across repeated memory encoding distinguishes memory formation of emotional and neutral events

  • run linear mixed models with linear increase predictor run, the factors emotion and subsequent memory and the random intercept of subject and item in anterior MTL

  • Estimate confidence intervalls for FDR-corrected, significant memory × run × emotion fixed effect estimates via Bootstrapping 1000 estimations utilizing parallelization

  • post hoc tests and marginal effects plots

    NOTE: result summary is printed by a function which always speaks of clusters, although here we have no clusters but individual regions

Mediation analysis

Amygdala activity at first exposure modulates emotional memory enhancement via neocortical pattern stability over repetitions

  1. run moderated mediation
  2. apply FDR correction
  3. find linear change in conditional indirect effects
  4. compute index of moderated mediation


results of oucome- and mediator-model

Estimating SPL encoding pattern stability by means of an LMM indicated:

a significant main effect emotion (ß = 0.019, t(6067.011) = 10.245, p < 0.001)
a significant interaction between emotion and initial amygdala activity (ß = 0.004, t(6074.029) = 2.154, p = 0.031)

Estimating subsequent free recall by means of a gLMM indicated:

a significant main effect emotion (ß = 0.711, z = 12.851, p < 0.001)
a significant main effect SPL pattern stability (ß = 2.505, z = 6.57, p < 0.001)
a significant interaction between emotion and initial amygdala activity (ß = 0.146, z = 2.593, p = 0.01)


results of conditional moderated mediation analysis

For low levels of the moderator, initial amygdala activity the conditional indirect effect of emotion on memory through SPL pattern similarity was 0.007 (CI[0.003, 0.012], pcorr < 0.001) with a direct effect of 0.125 (CI[0.092, 0.159], pcorr < 0.001), speaking for a partial mediation.

For average levels of the moderator, initial amygdala activity the conditional indirect effect of emotion on memory through SPL pattern similarity was 0.01 (CI[0.007, 0.014], pcorr < 0.001) with a direct effect of 0.156 (CI[0.133, 0.18], pcorr < 0.001), speaking for a partial mediation.

For high levels of the moderator, initial amygdala activity the conditional indirect effect of emotion on memory through SPL pattern similarity was 0.014 (CI[0.008, 0.02], pcorr < 0.001) with a direct effect of 0.186 (CI[0.152, 0.219], pcorr < 0.001), speaking for a partial mediation.


Figure 5, right panel: Initial amygdala aytivity significantly moderated emotional memory enhancement via superior parietal pattern stability
